JOHANNESBURG - The Edcon Group plans to appeal a decision by the National Consumer Tribunal declaring its club fee charged to credit consumers as unlawful.Edcon says it can't comment any further on the issue until it s been finalised.READ: Edcon club fee unlawful, finds tribunalThe National Consumer Tribunal says Edcon has been unlawfully charging a club fee to credit consumers since 2007.In a judgment handed down by the tribunal, it says charging consumers a fee for credit agreements contravenes the National Credit Act. The tribunal will request an independent audit of the Edcon Group s loan book to determine the number of consumers owed a refund.eNCA